  "history": "The client has a history of academic underperformance despite being described as intelligent, which may have contributed to ongoing self-doubt. They attended college but felt isolated, leading to dropping out with two years of credits remaining. The sense of isolation during college likely fostered feelings of loneliness and disconnection. The client faces financial difficulties and pressure from their mother to return home, which may increase stress and feelings of inadequacy. The mother’s high expectations appear to be a significant source of pressure and may have shaped the client’s self-evaluation and coping style.",
