  "intermediate_belief": "If I don't manage my time and achievements as well as my sister, then it means I'm not competent and will disappoint my family. I must always meet high standards to be worthy of approval. If I fall behind, others will see me as incapable.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I keep falling short and can't get myself together, there's no point in trying because I'll never measure up. My efforts are pointless if I can't meet expectations.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client tends to avoid academic tasks and withdraws from challenging situations, such as dropping out of college and not addressing scheduling problems. They engage in negative self-comparison and rumination about their perceived shortcomings, particularly in relation to their sister. These strategies maintain their distress and reinforce feelings of inadequacy.",
