  "behavior": "I avoid tackling my schedule and put off tasks. I spend time thinking about how much better my sister is doing. I withdraw from activities that remind me of my setbacks.",
  "rationale": "\"The patient may engage in negative self-comparisons, particularly with their sister, which can exacerbate feelings of inadequacy and self-doubt.\" \"The unproductive week due to scheduling problems might reinforce a belief of inefficacy, contributing to a cycle of procrastination and avoidance.\" \"Comparing themselves to their sister's achievements could result in feelings of inadequacy and low self-esteem, as they perceive themselves as falling short in comparison.\" \"In response to these emotional and cognitive experiences, the patient may engage in avoidance behaviors, such as withdrawing from academic pursuits and delaying their return to college.\""
